Text.Value: I want to free the Gondian hostages.
What hostages?
Halt.
The hostages are placed throughout this prison. You must stretch your resources thin if you want to secure them all.
Help or not - act quickly, or this Throne will be our tomb.
Normally I would find your people's lust for pleasantries amusing.
Get out of my head.
You would let innocents die? Shame on you. I will save everyone, just tell me how.
Act with speed. Act with efficiency. Good luck.
It is painful to say, but they cannot be your priority. Duke Ravengard MUST be saved. The city needs him.
Omeluum? Is that you?
Unfortunately, we have no time. The hostages need your help.
Fine, where is he?
You have arrived at an optimal time. Collapse is imminent, and there are hostages in need of aid.
I am here of my own accord. The hostages are not. Save them first.
Do not concern yourself with me. The city will be best served if you save Duke Ravengard.
Collateral. A threat to ensure Gortash's Steel Watch grip remains tight on the city.
I too feel this choice's... sorrow. But there are but a handful of hostages and Ravengard's survival will save thousands.
Duke Ravengard is held in the security wing.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We see a shot from Ravenguard's perspective, picking up on the desk in front of his cell and the long, green-lit corridor that leads to it
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Vision vignette induced by a mindmeld to justify showing a location that the player hasn't seen
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Vision vignette induced by a mindmeld to justify showing a location that the player hasn't seen

Text.Value: Tell me how to find them.
Where are you?
*A cold, suckering wetness grasps at your mind. A voice, familiar to you from the Underdark, wraps itself around your brain.*
Tell me what to do.
Be careful. There are many hazards. This structure is collapsing.
How do I get to the hostages?
I was only trying to secure this city's future... But you are correct. If we can, we should save the hostages too.
Unfortunately, we have no time. There are many hostages here. Duke Ravengard chief among them. He needs your help.
You must act with haste. Duke Ravengard is held within these walls. He must be extracted.

Synopsis: Omeluum mind melds with the player and asks for help and also reveals a mental visualization of the whole facility with indications for locations of hostages and enemies as well as any other useful information.
